This ransomware comes from a high volume spam campaign that aims to deliver this to as many users possible.

Hidden virtual network computing (HVNC) is a tactic that attempts to take control of a system via specific trojan modules. For example, Gozi has an HVNC module in order to use this kind of attack. Also this attack abuses Windows features such as CreateDesktop and cross-process window subclassing to implement an invisible environment for VNC to run.
